Program: Outlook
Title: 17/01/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00mvfvy
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 18 Jan 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, the Timorese teenager who was taken by Indonesian soldiers as a baby; 18 years on she discovered her real identity and set out to find her parents. Also, the former soldier who is still coming to terms with his actions in the South African Border War. And Ah Moon, a young singer with Burma's first Western-style girl group. Show less